Created `sample/01-cats-app/src/common/interceptors/response-time.interceptor.ts`.

The interceptor:
- Records `Date.now()` before the handler runs
- Uses `tap` (side-effect operator) to set the header after the handler completes
- Sets `X-Response-Time: <N>ms` on the response

To apply it globally in `main.ts` or locally on a controller:

```ts
// Global (main.ts)
app.useGlobalInterceptors(new ResponseTimeInterceptor());

// Or on a controller/route
@UseInterceptors(ResponseTimeInterceptor)
```

The `threshold` option (in milliseconds) is now supported. The header is only set when elapsed time exceeds it; with no threshold set, the header is always added:

```ts
// Always add the header (existing behaviour)
new ResponseTimeInterceptor()

// Only add the header when request takes longer than 200ms
new ResponseTimeInterceptor({ threshold: 200 })

// Custom header name + threshold
new ResponseTimeInterceptor({ headerName: 'X-Slow-Request', threshold: 500 })
```

